07/12/2009
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- NATO will continue its presence in Kosovo according to plan, the foreign ministers of the Alliance's member states agreed on Friday (December 4th) in Brussels. 
"Our KFOR mission ... 
is making a gradual, conditions-based transition to a deterrent posture, which we will keep under political review," the NATO ministers said in their final statement. 
(Koha Ditore, Zeri, Kohavision - 04/12/09)
